org.jlinalg.field_p

Class FieldP<RE extends FieldP<RE>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.RingElement<RE>
      • org.jlinalg.FieldElement<RE>
        • org.jlinalg.field_p.FieldP<RE>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<RE>, IRingElement<RE>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FieldPBig, FieldPLong

    public abstract class FieldP<RE extends FieldP<RE>>
extends FieldElement<RE>
    This class represents an element of the modulo p field Fp (i.e. the Galois field GF(p)) where p is prime. Fp is a field like any other field but there is no order that respects addition.
    Author:
    Andreas Lochbihler, Georg Thimm, Andreas Keilhauer
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • compareTo

        public abstract int compareTo(RE o)
        Compares this element with another element. o must be a instance of FieldP and its field must have the same number of elements as this' one. A element of Fp is considered to be smaller than a other element if and only if its smallest nonnegative representative is smaller than the other's one.
        Parameters:
        o - The object to compare to. Must be a instance of FieldP and of the same field Fp as this.
        Returns:
        < 0 if this is smaller than o, = 0 if this is equal to o (in the sense of equals), > 0 if this is bigger than o
